The paper deals with video classification using convolutional neural networks, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning approach, which involves exploiting unlabeled data, indicating that it could also belong to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of normalized probabilities, which could suggest that it belongs to the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on publicly available datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
